The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Sept. 30: Apollo Tyres Ltd today said it would divest its stake in the joint venture company, Michelin Apollo Tyres Pvt Ltd. The board of Michelin Apollo Tyres has approved the divestment of Apollo Tyres?s stake, which will be bought by the Michelin group and its affiliates, Apollo Tyres informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The board has also decided to defer the project to manufacture truck and bus radials in India by at least a year because it sees fewer takers for such tyres in the country.

 Mumbai, Sept. 30: The country?s external debt for the quarter ended June 30 declined by $1.3 billion to $122.1 billion compared with $123.4 billion at the end of the March quarter, the Reserve Bank said.

 New Delhi, Sept. 30: M.S. Darda has been appointed the new chairman of the Central Board of Direct Taxes. He is a member in the CBDT.

 Mumbai, Sept. 30: Air-India today selected DSP Merrill Lynch Ltd to be the advisor for its proposed initial public offering.

 New Delhi, Sept. 30: The government today extended the duty entitlement passbook (DEPB) scheme for a month, as the new duty neutralisation scheme is still being worked out, said Union finance minister P. Chidambaram.




